fields.physical_description:
1. 18-page photograph album, bound in cream and grey mottled paper
 with a front cover of tan suedette tooled and gilt with the title
 "SNAPSHOTS" in a rectangular frame above a yacht motif.
 2. landscape sepia photograph: mixed group of Canadian servicemen; 9.9
 x 12.3 cm
 3. portrait sepia snapshot: a woman holding a baby in a garden;
 inscribed "Doreen aged 5 months"; 8.7 x 6.2 cm
 4. portrait sepia snapshot: Archibald and Vera Kempson in a garden; 9
 x 6.3 cm
 5. portrait sepia snapshot: Sheila Youens in a garden with a dog;
 entitled "Sheila Age 8 yrs"; 9 x 6
 6. landscape sepia snapshot: Jack Youens in a deckchair in the garden
 with Sheila Youens aged about 4 perched on his knee; 8.4 x 6 cm 7.
 portrait sepia snapshot: Ella Youens in a deckchair in the garden with
 a dark-coated dog; 8.4 x 6 cm       8.
 portrait sepia snapshot: Sheila Youens aged about 3 on the beach with
 Jack Youens in a deckchair in the background; entitled "Sheila"; 8.4 x
 5.8 cm
 9. portrait sepia snapshot: Jack Youens in a deckchair in the garden
 with a dark-coated dog; 8.4 x 6 cm
 10. portrait sepia photograph: Mary Kempson at about 3, by a deckchair
 in the garden; 8 x 6 cm
 11. portrait sepia snapshot: Sheila Youens sitting in a wicker chair
 in the garden with a pull-along toy and a ball on the grass beside
 her; 8.3 x 5.9 cm
 12. portrait sepia snapshot: Peter Elmes, Sheila Youens and Mary
 Kempson in the garden with a dolls' pram, with Doris Elmes in the
 background; 8.4 x 6 cm
 13. landscape sepia snapshot: Archibald & Vera Kempson, Jack Youens,
 Doris & Lawrence Elmes with the children Peter Elmes, Sheila Youens &
 Mary Kempson in front, all in the garden; 6.1 x 8.6 cm
 14. portrait sepia snapshot: Vera Kempson in a chair in the garden
 with her baby daughter Mary on her lap and her niece Sheila Youens
 standing beside her; 8.5 x 6 cm
 15. portrait sepia snapshot: Ella Youens in a chair in the garden with
 her baby niece Mary on her lap and her daughter Sheila standing beside
 her; 8.55 x 6.05 cm
 16. portrait sepia snapshot: Archibald Kempson as a young man; 8.6 x
 5.3 cm
 17. portrait sepia snapshot: Kathleen Youens in a chair in the garden
 with her baby grand-daughter Mary Kempson on her lap; 8.5 x 5.9 cm
 18. landscape sepia snapshot: Archibald & Vera Kempson in the garden
 with their baby daughter Mary; 5.9 x 8.5 cm
 19. landscape sepia snapshot: Betty Dunnett (Mary Kempson's second
 cousin) sitting astride a toy lion in the garden; inscribed "Betty 1
 year 10 mth"; 6 x 8.3 cm
 20. portrait sepia snapshot: Anne Batcheler & her younger sister
 Penelope with an arm round each other in the garden, Anne holding a
 baby doll; 8.55 x 6.1 cm
 21. landscape sepia snaphshot: Anne & Penelope Batcheler with their
 mother Freda at the seaside; inscribed "Wales. Aug 1941 The hut we
 stayed in is behind Anne's head."; 5.8 x 8.3 cm
 22. portrait sepia snapshot: unknown little girl in a bridesmaid's or
 fancy dress outfit (long dress, cap and mittens) holding a spray of
 flowers and standing in a garden; 8.6 x 6.1 cm
 23. portrait sepia snapshot: unknown woman, with Sheila Youens in a
 pushchair out of doors; 8.6 x 5.8 cm
 24. portrait sepia snapshot: Archibald & Vera Kempson in a doorway;
 8.4 x 6.15 cm
 25. portrait sepia snapshot: Archibald & Vera Kempson walking hand in
 hand; captioned on back "WALKING PICTURES"; 7.6 x 5.8 cm
 26. portrait sepia photograph: Archibald Kempson; inscribed Sept 1931;
 8.8 x 6.2 cm
 27. portrait sepia snapshot: unknown man on a beach; 8.8 x 5.7 cm
 28. portrait sepia snapshot: unknown woman & girl; 7.7 x 5.7 cm
 29. portrait sepia snapshot: Vera & Archibald Kempson in a doorway;
 6.6 x 4.5 cm
 30. portrait sepia snapshot: Vera & Archibald Kempson outside a house;
 6.6 x 4.4 cm
 31. landscape sepia snapshot: Archibald & Vera Kempson walking arm in
 arm in the street; 6 x 4.4 cm
 32. squared sepia snapshot: Archibald & Vera Kempson in a garden; 6.5
 x 6.4 cm
 33. portrait sepia snapshot: Doris Elmes sitting on a bench with her
 son Peter; 6.9 x 4.4 cm
 34. portrait sepia snapshot: Peter Elmes standing by a fence; 6.6 x
 4.3 cm
 35. landscape sepia snapshot: unknown man, woman & girl; 4.3 x 6.3 cm
 36. portrait sepia snapshot: a baby (probably Mary Kempson) in a pram
 outside a house; 6.9 x 4.3 cm
 37. portrait sepia snapshot: unknown baby (probably Mary Kempson) in a
 basket; 6.6 x 4.4 cm
 38. portrait sepia snapshot: Mary Kempson with an unknown little girl
 outside the same building in Addingham as in B.289:58-1994; 8.4 x 13.6
 cm
 39. portrait sepia snapshot: Archibald Kempson in a field;7.5 x 5.3 cm
 40. portrait sepia snapshot: Archibald Kempson sitting on a fence
 among trees; 6.8 x 4.3 cm
 41. landscape sepia snapshot: a church in parkland; 4.3 x 6.3 cm
 42. landscape sepia snapshot: 4 unknown adults outside a building; 6.3
 x 8.9 cm
 43. portrait sepia snapshot: Vera Kempson standing by some trees; 6.6
 x 4.4 cm
 44. portrait sepia snapshot: Rosemary Batcheler standing by a table in
 a garden; inscribed "Rosemary Batcheler July 1945 2 yrs"; 8.9 x 6.3 cm
 45. landscape sepia photograph: two youths (the one on the right
 probably Archibald Kempson) in three-piece suits, sitting on a bench
 by a wall; 10.12.5 cm
fields.dimensions: Height: 12.8 cm album, Width: 17 cm shut, Depth: 1.3 cm
fields.title: SNAPSHOTS
fields.history_note:
References: 


The prints show the donor (b 06/1937), members of her
family (see B.289-1994 for details of names and
relationships)
